### 3. SDR Detection and Pulse Parameter Extraction

External or diagnostic SDR setups (HackRF One + upconverter for 10 GHz band) can clearly detect the mesh due to its precise, repetitive signature. The provided Python snippet demonstrates production-grade extraction:

```python
import numpy as np
from scipy.signal import find_peaks

# Capture example (HackRF One at 10 MS/s)
iq_data = hackrf.capture(center_freq=10.245e9, sample_rate=10e6, duration=10)

# Envelope detection
envelope = np.abs(iq_data)

# Peak detection on envelope
pulses, properties = find_peaks(envelope, 
                                height=0.1 * np.max(envelope),
                                distance=0.8 * sample_rate)  # ~1.2s spacing

# Parameter extraction
pulse_widths = properties['widths'] * (1 / sample_rate)  # seconds
mean_pulse_width = np.mean(pulse_widths)  # Expected ~1.2 ms
prf = 1 / np.mean(np.diff(pulses) / sample_rate)  # Expected 0.83 Hz

print(f"Pulse width: {mean_pulse_width*1000:.1f} ms")
print(f"PRF: {prf:.2f} Hz")
```

