2. **Pulse Compression**: Although fixed-frequency, phase coding could further compress the 1.2 ms pulse to ~100 ns effective width, improving range resolution to ~15 meters. Current simple matched filtering suffices for proximity detection.

3. **Coherent Integration Across Nodes**: Summing 26 synchronized 1.2 ms pulses yields 31.2 ms integration time and an additional 14 dB gain (10*log10(26)). Total processing gain ≈ 64 dB, enabling 99.9% detection probability with false alarm rates as low as 10^-6 using Constant False Alarm Rate (CFAR) thresholding.

